learning_outcomes.en:
On successful completion of the unit, students will be able to:
- appreciate some of the central issues in semiotic approach to mediation, multimedial and performative arts and texts;
- demonstrate knowledge of the key concepts, models and issues introduced during the course;
- describe semiotic aspects of a phenomena in hand and choose relevant concepts and models for analysing them;
- read the relevant texts critically and reflexively and be able to identify problems arising from them; withdraw the most important concepts of a theoretical texts and defend his/her position in a discussion;
- understand different cultural events which can be analysed as performances or instances of mediation;
- know and can apply different semiotic approaches in analysis of multimedial relations and performativity in texts and in culture;
- discriminate, combine and describe different semiotic modalities and analyse their interaction in meaning construction both in multimedial and performative texts;
- break down and also compose multimedial and performative texts, evaluate the influence and role of author, receiver and context when analysing or constucting the text;

learning_outcomes.et:
Loengu läbinud üliõpilane:
1) suudab tekstidest olulisima välja tuua kaitstes oma seisukohti diskussioonis;
2) õpib kehalise eneseväljenduse vahendusel isiklikku kogemust analüüsima;
3) teab etenduse uuringute ajalugu, tunneb semiootilist ning fenomenoloogilist lähenemist;
4) saab aru erinevatest etenduse all mõistetud kultuurinähtustest;
5) teab ja oskab rakendada erinevaid semiootilisi lähenemisi tekstide multimeedialiste suhete analüüsimisel;
6) eraldab, kombineerib ja kirjeldab erinevaid semiootilisi modaalsusi ning analüüsib nende interaktsiooni tähenduse konstrueerimisel;
7) suudab luua multimediaalset teksti ning hinnata autori, vastuvõtja ja konteksti mõju ja rolli teksti analüüsimisel või konstrueerimisel.

description.et:
The criteria of assesment for written analysis
A - the object chosen is excellent for analysis of multimediality or performativity; analysis is very detailed and comprehensive; theoretical texts used for the analysis are relevant for the topic, the concepts used in a well-defined, the argumentation clear and well-structured, the author's own synthesis original, scientifically correct presentation of the text;
B - the object chosen is suitable for analysis of multimediality or performativity; analysis is thorough, detailed and comprehensive; correct use of terms, the theoretical texts used relevant for the topic, original ideas present, minor gaps in argumentation, presentation or structuring of the text;
C - the object chosen is rather suitable for analysis of multimediality or performativity; analysis is well made and gives good overview of the multimedial or performative issues at hand; the use of concepts not fully consistent, the line of argumentation tracable but further comments needed, problems with the integrity of the text;
D - the object chosen might not be quite as suitable for analysis of multimediality or performativity; the analysis is not very comprehensive and discusses some of the multimedial or performative issues at hand; the central concepts irrelevant or not well defined, larger gaps in binding different parts of the text together, the theoretical works not fully relevant, the text lacks originality;
E - the object chosen is not very suitable for analysis of multimediality or performativity; the analysis is sketchy and discusses few of the relevant multimedial or performative issues; the argumentation of the text hard to follow, no relevant references, the text is unstructured and the presentation does not fully follow the academic standards;
F - the object chosen is not suitable for analysis of multimediality or performativity; analysis is lacking or irrelevant; no signs of logical argumentation, originality or academic structuring principles, concerning both the form as well as the content;

grade_evaluation.et:
The criteria of assesment for attendence, activity
A - attended in all lectures and seminars, participated actively in discussions;
B - attended in 90% of lectures and seminars, participated actively in discussions;
C - attended in 75% of lectures and seminars, participated in discussions;
D - attended in 60% of lectures and seminars, at times participated in discussions;
E - attended in 50% of lectures and seminars, little participation in discussions;
F - attended in less than 50% of lectures and seminars, no acitve participation in discussions;
